
[1]rigging

   RIG'GING, ppr. Dressing; fitting with shrouds, braces, &c.

   RIG'GING, n. Dress; tackle; particularly, the ropes which support the
   masts, extend and contract the sails, &c. of a ship. This is of two
   kinds, standing rigging, as the shrouds and stays, and running rigging,
   such as braces, sheets, halliards, clewlines, &c.
